<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8430721>
    dc:description "FIGURES 13–25. (13–16). Maladera allopruinosa (Ahrens, 1998) (Purba Bardhaman, West Bengal); (17–21). Maladera bengalensis (Brenske, 1898) (West Champaran, Bihar); (22–25). Maladera burmeisteri burmeisteri (Brenske, 1898) (Purba bardhaman, west Bengal); (13, 17, 22) Aedeagus in lateral view (left); (14, 18, 23) Aedeagus in dorsal view; (19) Aedeagus in ventral view; (15, 20, 24) Aedeagus in lateral view (right); (16, 21, 25) Habitus, dorsal view. Scale 0.5 mm. Habitus not to scale." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8430721/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8430745>
    dc:description "FIGURE 98. (A–B). A. Gangetic plains biogeographic zone of India; B. Map of Lower Gangetic plains showing sample localities of the species: Maladera kolkataensis, Gynaecoserica perdita, Maladera affinis, M. allopruinosa, M. bengalensi, M. burmeisteri burmeisteri, M. cardoni." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8430745/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

